Mexican Stocks: Grupo Elektra, Grupo Financiero Inbursa, Vitro

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-07-29T18:00:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/mexican-stocks-grupo-elektra-grupo-financiero-inbursa-vitro.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:23 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.4 percent to 36,051.87.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM) surged 4.9 percent to 861.83
pesos, a record high, as the Mexico City-based retail and
banking company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas  sold
$400 million of bonds due in 2018 to yield 7.5 percent,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Grupo Financiero Inbursa SAB (GFINBURO MM), the Mexican
financial group owned by billionaire  Carlos Slim , gained 0.2
percent to 56.44 pesos as Frank Aguado, its chief of credit,
said it plans to sell as much as 24 billion pesos ($2 billion)
of local bonds by March as it seeks long-term funding. Aguado
spoke on a conference call with analysts.  Vitro SAB (VITROA MM), the Mexican glassmaker that
defaulted on $1.2 billion of bonds, advanced 1.2 percent to
11.40 pesos as the company based in the Monterrey suburb of San
Pedro Garza Garcia,  Mexico , posted a profit in the second-
quarter on the back of higher beer bottle sales after reporting
losses for the previous three quarters.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
